messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
I have a little girl who fell in the pool and I think she's unconscious right now.
Okay. What is the address?
It's 886 East Florida Avenue.
What city are you in?
Denver, Colorado.
Alright, let me get you in touch with Denver. Do not hang up.
Okay, hold on one moment.
I will stay on the phone.
Jennifer 911, 8274. How may I help you?
Hi, this is Diva with Aurora. I've got a lady on the phone who might possibly have an unconscious child. 886 East Florida Avenue. Is that going to be yours?
East Florida? Yes. Is the child breathing?
She's 12 years old. She's not breathing. She's not doing anything.
Alright, ma'am, hold on. I'm getting some help for you. Hold on.
She's not doing anything. What do we do? Is there anything we can do?
Is she out of the pool?
Yes, she's out of the pool.
Okay, I need you to lay her on her back.
We did. We laid her on her back.
Is she on a flat surface?
Yes, she's on a flat surface.
Alright, place one hand on her forehead and your other hand under her chin. Tilt her head back to open her airway.
Okay, I'm doing that.
Ma'am, I'm going to give you instructions to help her breathe. Can you do CPR?
I don't think I can do it.
Is there someone else there who can?
I'm the only one here and there's a little child only.
Okay, can you give the phone to the child, or can I walk you through CPR?
I don't see anybody else. It's just the child and she's my neighbor.
Can you try to do CPR? I will guide you through it.
Okay, I will try.
First, lay her flat on her back on a hard surface. Tilt her head back to open her airway. Can you do that?
Yes, I already did that.
Is she breathing?
I think she is.
Can you see her chest rising and falling?
Yeah.
What is the color of her face and lips?
Her lips are red and her face looks normal.
But she's still unconscious, correct?
Yes.
Help is on the way. I want to make sure she is breathing though. Is it normal breathing or is she gasping for air?
She's gasping for air.
Right now she is?
Yes.
Describe to me how she is breathing.
She's gasping and breathing hard.
Okay, hold on. Help is on the way.
